issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
I use huggingface transformers albert model albert-base-v2 to classify text,meanwhile,I use onnxruntime to optimized and quantized，

`opt_model = optimizer.optimize_model(
    'onnx/albert_chinese_base.onnx',
    'bert',
    num_heads=12,
    hidden_size=768,
    optimization_options=opt_options)
opt_model.save_model_to_file('albert.opt.onnx')`

`quantized_model_path = quantize(Path("albert.opt.onnx"))`
the optimized result is the same with origin result， but the quantized result is different from origin result，as follows：
origin result as follows:
tensor([[ -4.9603,  -9.1380, -12.4145,  -2.8629,  -2.9166, -14.1528,  -0.7807,
          -1.6513,  -8.1648,  12.1220]])
quantized result as follows:
tensor([[ -5.6812, -11.3905, -21.9474,   0.0971,  -8.1226, -19.2604,   1.3498,
          -9.9139, -16.5754,   5.7205]])

**System information**
onnx               1.8.1
onnxruntime        1.6.0
onnxruntime-tools  1.6.0
transformers       4.3.3

body:
hi @jianqianzhou, onnxruntime_tools currently supports hugginface Albert onnx optimization exported from pytorch model. We plan to support tf model in the near future. 
You may need to disable attention fusion to walk around this issue.
BTW, opt_options = BertOptimizationOptions('bert_tf') is the right API to setup optimization for tf model from the current implementation.

> hi @jianqianzhou, onnxruntime_tools currently supports hugginface Albert onnx optimization exported from pytorch model. We plan to support tf model in the near future.
> You may need to disable attention fusion to walk around this issue.
> BTW, opt_options = BertOptimizationOptions('bert_tf') is the right API to setup optimization for tf model from the current implementation.

I modify BertOptimizationOptions ，but the Error is the same：
onnxruntime.capi.onnxruntime_pybind11_state.Fail: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 1 : FAIL : Load model from segment.opt.onnx failed:This is an invalid model. Node (StatefulPartitionedCall/tf_albert_model/albert/encoder/albert_layer_groups_._0/albert_layers_._0/attention/add) input arg (StatefulPartitionedCall/tf_albert_model/albert/mul:0) does not have type information set by parent node.

`

opt_options = BertOptimizationOptions('bert_tf')
opt_options.enable_embed_layer_norm = False

opt_model = optimizer.optimize_model(
    output_model_path,
    'bert_keras',
    num_heads=12,
    hidden_size=768,
    optimization_options=opt_options)
opt_model.save_model_to_file('segment.opt.onnx')`

Hi, @wangyems :)
